    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf a filetype has ftplugin with `vim.treesitter.start()` (e.g, lua and markdown out of box) plus `syntax on`, neovim will skip certain events when opening file using `nvim <file>`.\n\nNote that user ftplugin for the filetype is also skipped.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- init.lua\n\nvim.cmd('syntax on')\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufRead', {\n  callback = function(ctx) BufRead = 'foo' end,\n})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufReadPre', {\n  callback = function(ctx) BufReadPre = 'foo' end,\n})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufEnter', {\n  callback = function(ctx) BufEnter = 'foo' end,\n})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\n  callback = function(ctx) FileType = 'foo' end,\n})\n```\n\nThen open `init.lua` with(because `lua` already have `vim.treesitter.start` on its ftplugin by default)\n\n```sh\nnvim --clean -u init.lua init.lua\n```\n\nThen inspect those indicator value(`nil` means the event is not executed):\n\n```vim\n=BufRead \" nil\n=BufReadPre \" nil\n=BufEnter \" foo\n=FileType \" nil\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThose event(as well as user ftplugin) should be executed as expected.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-499+g6780e78b09\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot related\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux nixos 6.6.114.1-microsoft-standard-WSL2 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Mon Dec  1 20:46:23 UTC 2025 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20260117-154428-05343b38\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ndirect unpacked tar",
